AWKA – It was a black Saturday in Ebenebe, Awka North Local Government Area, of Anambra State, as armed men suspected to be cultists invaded the community during a funeral, killing over 25 people. This Paper gathered that it was the burial of a suspected leader of a cultist named Ozo, and while the corpse of Ozo was lying in state in his compound, some suspected cultists arrived on the scene and sacked the mourners by shooting. Narrating her ordeal during the incident an eyewitness who spoke on how she escaped death, said that she was about to get seated when these dreaded cultists arrived at the burial ceremony and started shooting randomly at everybody APC Crisis Heightens As Court Voids APC Congress In Anambra Anambra Bars Heavy Duty Trucks From Plying Agulu Lake Bridge He managed to escape and ran to the opposite house where he managed to view what is happening. There was heavy shooting which made everybody at the burial to be dispersed by gunmen. According to her, before she could run out of the scene, the news had escalated and even the videos had gone viral “She also got a video from the scene, which showed several persons lying in the pool of their own blood dead, while the corpse was desecrated, with its coffin lying far apart, the corpse.”A video was seen with members of the community wailing, while corpses littered the burial compound.Reacting, the Anambra State Police Command has confirmed the incident, saying that it was a case of cult rivalry.According to the Command’s spokesperson, DSP Toochukwu Ikenga, he said: “Yes, this ..morning, there was an incident at Ebenebe. A burial was going on when some people suspected to be cultists invaded the area and started shooting. NOTE: Pictures of the bodies of victims and the desecrated corpse in the casket could not be uploaded here for the reason of decorum.